^B@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|Whenever I pick up my cards, I always think about the following:

^*B|va|2|at|^bMy first impression. Is the hand upgradeable, downgradable, or will its true value be the same as it appears to be?
|va|2|at|^bNext I count my formal number of HCP just as a beginner would.
|va|2|at|^bI add for long suits, 5 cards or more. With a suit of 7 cards or more I add more liberally. 
|va|2|at|^b@2I Upgrading For Long Strong Suits.
|va|2|at|^b@2I Devalue Honors In Short Suits.
|va|2|at|^bI Have My Starting Points.
|va|2|at|^bThe Rule Of 20
|va|2|at|^bI Mind the Distribution.
|va|2|at|^bI Look at My Intermediates.
|va|2|at|^bI consider the location of my honors and intermediates.
|va|2|at|^bNT Opening Bids.
|va|2|at|^bI Count My Quick Tricks.
|va|2|at|^bIndependent Suits|

ht|t|at|^b@2Evaluating your hand before the auction begins is a very important first step. Reevaluating your hand as the auction proceeds is even more important. Most players do not do a good job in this area.^*N|
